premise_source_doc_sentence: Pope Celestine V  (  Caelestinus V 1215 -- 19 May 1296  )  , born Pietro Angelerio  (  according to some sources Angelario , Angelieri , Angelliero , or Angeleri  )  , also known as Pietro da Morrone , Peter of Morrone , and Peter Celestine , was Pope for five months from 5 July to 13 December 1294 , when he resigned .

premise_source_doc_sentence: Celestine was canonized on 5 May 1313 by Pope Clement V. No subsequent pope has taken the name Celestine .
